value.value: Each of the discrete cells in the cuticular sculpture of rigid surfaces in spiders such as some Araneoidea.
The claw lever of leg 1.
The claw lever of leg 2.
The claw lever of leg 3.
The claw lever of leg 4.
The cheliceral escort seta on the promargin.
The cheliceral escort seta on the retromargin.
The 7th, most distal article of the female palp, articulated with the tarsus and containing the claw.
A mechanoreceptor sensitive to strain on the cuticle. It has a linear shape with raised borders. Slit sensilla may occur in isolation or in groups of parallel sensilla, forming a lyriform organ.
Each of the sclerites forming a ring, where the coxal and trochanter muscles insert. Upon leg autospasy, the cleavage occurs across the sclerites, thus leaving the coxal muscles intact.
A group of short propiosensory setae placed at the ventral basal corners of coxae. They are reflected by the folding of the pleural membrane.
A propiosensor made of a group of parallel slit sensilla.
A lyriform organ placed just behind the metatarsus dorsal stopper, with slit sensilla perpendicular to the leg axis.
A paired lateral-ventral slit sensilla at the tip of the tarsus, sensitive to vibrations. It delimits the foot.

Each of the several long, elongate setae, with strong socket and smooth shaft, occurring anteriorly on the opisthosoma around the pedicel. They are presumably propioceptors of the position of the opisthosoma relative to the prosoma.
A barb with expanded tip that makes contact with substratum and produces adherence through molecular forces.
A seta with a defined patch of tenent barbs, such as those of the scopula or claw tuft.
A patch of chemosensory setae apically on the dorsal surface of the female palpal tarsus.
A patch of chemosensory setae apically on the dorsal surface of the male palpal tarsus (cymbium). It has been shown to be sensitive to the pheromones laid by females in draglines.
A seta with intermediate morphology between tenent and tactile hair, with acute tip and tenent barbs loosely organized on the contact side but usually not forming a pad.
The shaft of a scale.
The socket of a scale.
The socket of the chemosensory seta.
A mesh of cuticular extensions lining the booklung atrium and the base of booklung leaves.
A fold connecting the booklung atria from each side, lined by a mesh of cuticular extensions.
An internal prolongation of the cuticle where muscles insert.
A trachea of small diameter with single cuticular wall, without internal mesh.
The entapophysis of the second opisthosomal segment.
The entapophysis of the fourth opisthosomal segment.
The entapophysis of the fifth opisthosomal segment.
A sensillum whose dendrites end on a pore in the cuticle, sensitive to its deformations.

A flexible piece at the tip of the spigot shaft, delimiting the apical opening. It has been reported in the spigots of Polenecia producta (Uloboridae) but has a wider, scattered distribution in other taxa as well.
The opisthosomal segment bearing the anal tubercle.
A internal cuticular tube inside the chemosensory seta shaft, enclosing the dentrites, extending from the apical pore to about 2/3 of the shaft length.
The division of the copulatory bulb between the basal and median hematodochae, containing the subtegulum.
The division of the copulatory bulb between the median and terminal hematodochae, containing the tegulum, conductor and median apophysis.
A sclerite connecting the embolus with the tegulum through the terminal hematodocha, and containing the spermophor.
Any of the sclerotized processes arising in the cymbium.
A sclerotized process on the male palpal tibia.
A process on the middle of the ventral surface of the male palpal femur.
A process on the ventral surface of the male palpal femur near its base.
A process on the ventral surface of the male palpal femur near its distal end.
A process on the dorsal surface of the male palpal patella.
A process on the retrolateral surface of the male palpal patella.
A gland inside the male palpal tibia, discharging through a pore on a tibial process. Has been found in some Spartaeinae (Saliticidae) and Macrobuninae (Amaurobiidae).
A ventral longitudinal groove on the tip of the cymbium. It occurs in Anyphaenidae.
A longitudinal groove on the retrolateral surface of cymbium. It occurs in several Miturgidae.

label.value: male palpal tibia dorsal basal process

value.value: A proximal process on the dorsal surface of the male palpal tibia.

label.value: male palpal tibia ventral apical process

value.value: A distal process on the ventral surface of the male palpal tibia.
A spermatheca on the anterior section of the female genitalia.
